https://www.reddit.com/r/dailyprogrammer/comments/7vm223/20180206_challenge_350_easy_bookshelf_problem/

plan:
sort shelves biggest to smallest
sort books biggest to smallest

Fill largest shelf with largest books until the next one does fit.
Then find the biggest one that would fit in available space.
Repeat until no other books would fit.
Move to the next largest shelf and repeat.

OUTPUT:
$ ./bookshelf.py 
Bookshelf problem
Shelves: 97
Books: 115
Shelves Used: 13
